@NODE "History"
@NEXT "Team"
@PREV "Main"
@TOC "Main"

@{b}Fly By Nite Videe-Oh!@{ub} began its life as a video production company
for my home movies.  The name stuck and I used it for all my subsequent
projects.

Over the years, quite a few @{"people" LINK "Team"} have played a part in the
FBN activities.

FBN began with my Commodore 64 computer and Movie Maker by Electronic Arts.
It has progressed to my Amiga computer using a large variety of programs.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Team"
@NEXT "Garak"
@PREV "History"
@TOC "Main"

The main players in the FBN world are @{"Garak" LINK "Garak"}, @{"Shape Shifter" LINK "SS"} and
@{"joe hick" LINK "joe"}.

I'm Giark (Guy-Ark).  I began FBN as a name for my movies and such like.
I've been making movies of one type or another for 19 years and have been
programming for 13 years.  You can contact me on @{"CyberSpace BBS" LINK "CyberSpace"} where,
as well as managing the FBN and @{"AMOS" LINK "Amos"} support areas, I am CoSys.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Garak"
@NEXT "SS"
@PREV "Team"
@TOC "Main"

Garak joined the FBN team in 1994 and was the co-writer of @{"SoloTrek" LINK "Solotrek"}.
He is currently in his final year of high school and is working in a joint
effort on the sequel to @{"SoloTrek" LINK "Solotrek"}, @{"ModemTrek" LINK "Modemtrek"}.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "SS"
@NEXT "joe"
@PREV "Garak"
@TOC "Main"

What can I say about Shape Shifter?  He has been instrumental in the FBN
motion pictures, as well as a willing co-conspirator in the now infamous
Black September debacle.  (Not really.  I made that up.)  You might
recognize him from his role in the FBN Blockbuster @{"ScrollQuest" LINK "Scrollquest"}.
The MOD Winky Commander was written with SS in mind.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "joe"
@NEXT "CyberSpace"
@PREV "SS"
@TOC "Main"

joe hick is the SysOp of @{"CyberSpace BBS" LINK "Cyberspace"} and has been very helpful
by allowing me to test @{"Lunar Conquest" LINK "Lunar"} on his board.

@ENDNODE

