@NODE "Multimedia"
@NEXT "Videos"
@PREV "Amos"
@TOC "Main"

As the years progressed and technology became cheaper, FBN expanded into
the print market.  This made FBN a truly multimedia company (Print, Disk,
Video, Audio, etc.)

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Videos"
@NEXT "Star"
@PREV "Multimedia"
@TOC "Main"

FBN has been involved in many different productions over the years.  In the
early years, movie production was on 8mm film with no sound.  At that time,
the company went under the name of Leadstar Newt productions.  The best of
the LN films was the hilarious (in retrospect) copy of @{"Star Wars" LINK "Star"} that
contains the famous three pass kissing scene and the `Chewie wants a banana'
segment.

Among the video titles are the Sheridan family series, The Texas Instruments,
The Rhinos - Live! and Conestoga Homegrown.

@{" Star Wars         " LINK "Star"}
@{" Texas Instruments " LINK "Texas"}
@{" ScrollQuest       " LINK "Scrollquest"}
@{" Rocket Commandos  " LINK "Rocket"}
@{" Vampire!          " LINK "Vampire"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Star"
@NEXT "Texas"
@PREV "Videos"
@TOC "Main"

Star Wars

Shot in silent 8mm format, this is one of the wierdest films that FBN has
been involved in to date.  Watch for the spinning christmas lights of the
hyperspace segment and the funky tartan blanket used for Darth Vader's
cloak.  No, that's not a lightsaber, it's a hockey stick!

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Texas"
@NEXT "Scrollquest"
@PREV "Star"
@TOC "Main"

Out Of The Basement, Into The Attic: The Texas Instruments Reunion Concert

Another in the genre of `fake band rockumentaries' like `This Is Spinal Tap',
`The Ruttles' and others.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Scrollquest"
@NEXT "Rocket"
@PREV "Texas"
@TOC "Main"

Scrollquest marked FBN's entry into high tech production.  The entire musical
score was composed by me (Giark) and produced using the Amiga.  Another
member of the FBN team made his presence known in Scrollquest: The Master,
who plays Lex Farslayer.

ScrollQuest is the story of a group of young barbarians who must try to
recover the scroll of doom.

Cost: $15 Cdn.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Rocket"
@NEXT "Vampire"
@PREV "Scrollquest"
@TOC "Main"

Rocket Commandos is yet another technological leap for the FBN crew.  The
special effects are being produced using rendering technology which is also
used on tv shows and movies, such as Babylon 5, SeaQuest and Jurassic Park.

Rocket Commandos is currently on hold due to production difficulties and
other technical considerations.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Vampire"
@NEXT "Programs"
@PREV "Rocket"
@TOC "Main"

Vampire!

Currently in pre-production, Vampire! is the next FBN movie.  It will be
shot in the summer of 1996 and should be released by September `96.

@ENDNODE

