@NODE "Therapy"
@NEXT "Blackjack"
@PREV "Programs"
@TOC "Main"
Name: Therapy
Type: Game
Info: Therapy is a copy of an old VIC-20 program of the same name.  It has
been enhanced by graphics and synthesized speech.  You'll enjoy playing with
Dr. Synthetic Freud.

This game is freeware.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Blackjack"
@NEXT "Banner"
@PREV "Therapy"
@TOC "Main"
Name: Blackjack For The Master
Type: Game
Info: The Master was trying to write a blackjack program and was having a
bit of difficulty so I cobbled together this one for him.  After he had
checked out the source, I compiled it and released it under the FBN label.
The game is fairly simple, with quite impressive card graphics.

This game is freeware.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Banner"
@NEXT "Dungeon"
@PREV "Blackjack"
@TOC "Main"
Name: Banner
Type: Utility
Info: Banner is another copy of a VIC-20 program.  It uses an IFF picture
of a character set to produce 80 column high banners on your printer.

This utility is freeware.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Dungeon"
@NEXT "Solotrek"
@PREV "Banner"
@TOC "Main"
Name: Dungeon
Type: Game
Info: Dungeon is an over the modem game (registered version) similar to
those found in the early days of computing.  You and your opponent are in
a large arena filled with monsters and treasures.  Your object is to kill
the other player before he kills you.

This game is cardware.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Solotrek"
@NEXT "Demo"
@PREV "Dungeon"
@TOC "Main"
Name: SoloTrek
Type: Game
Info: SoloTrek is a Star Trek combat simulator with several difficulty
levels and digitized sounds.  The graphics are fair and the game play is
quite smooth.

This game is freeware.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Demo"
@NEXT "Lunar"
@PREV "Solotrek"
@TOC "Main"
Name: CyberSpace BBS Demo
Type: Demo
Info: Created as an ad for @{"CyberSpace BBS" LINK "Cyberspace"}, this program contains
rendered screens and objects, plasma effects and two original MODs:
ST-NightGroove and Winky Commander.

This demo is freeware.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Lunar"
@NEXT "Inform"
@PREV "Demo"
@TOC "Main"
Name: Lunar Conquest
Type: Online Game
Info: Lunar Conquest is based on an Atari ST game.  It has been tested on
the CNet 3.0+ BBS and runs quite well.

This game is shareware.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Inform"
@NEXT "Reminder"
@PREV "Lunar"
@TOC "Main"
Name: Inform Tool
Type: Utility
Info: Inform tool is a utility to aid in the use of the Inform Compiler
which is used to write Infocom type games.

This utility is freeware.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Reminder"
@NEXT "DungeonV2"
@PREV "Inform"
@TOC "Main"
Name: Reminder
Type: Nagger/Reminder
Info: Reminder is an appointment book which runs under intuition and keeps
track of your important events and reminds you of them.

This utility is freeware.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "DungeonV2"
@NEXT "DungeonV2Mod"
@PREV "Reminder"
@TOC "Main"
Name: Dungeon V2
Type: Game
Info: Another follow-up, Dungeon V2 is a major upgrade to the limited but
still fun @{"Dungeon" LINK "Dungeon"}.  Dungeon V2 features custom files for different
maps to be used for play and the setting of other goals.  Full ansi color
and graphics are supported.  As before, the other player need only have
an ANSI terminal program to play the game.

Included in the Dungeon V2 archive is the @{"Classic" LINK "Classic"} module.  This allows game
play similar to that of the original Dungeon.  Additional @{"modules" LINK "DungeonV2Mod"} are being
created every day.

This game is shareware with a cost of $15.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "DungeonV2Mod"
@NEXT "Classic"
@PREV "DungeonV2"
@TOC "Main"

At this point, there is no map creator for Dungeon V2, so all the modules are
coming direct from FBN's programming division.  If enough interest is
generated, a Map Creator program will be created and sent to all registered
users.

The modules currently offered are:

@{" Classic                " LINK "Classic"}
@{" Alien Derelict         " LINK "AlienDerelict"}
@{" The Riddle Of Chang Ku " LINK "ChangKu"}
@{" The House Of Fright    " LINK "HouseOfFright"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Classic"
@NEXT "AlienDerelict"
@PREV "DungeonV2Mod"
@TOC "Main"

The original Dungeon map lives on in the Dungeon V2 Classic module.  It's a
ten by ten map with all the monsters, potions, weapons and armour faithfully
reproduced from the original Dungeon game.

This module is included with the Dungeon V2 archive.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "AlienDerelict"
@NEXT "ChangKu"
@PREV "Classic"
@TOC "Main"

You're stuck on an alien ship packed with monsters from SciFi movies.  Grab a
weapon and start blasting!  Find the code key and get into an escape pod to
win this challenging game.  This module includes a custom sound file and an
intro music module.

This module is shareware at a cost of $2 and requires the Dungeon V2 archive
to work.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "ChangKu"
@NEXT "HouseOfFright"
@PREV "AlienDerelict"
@TOC "Main"

Alone in the ancient ruins of the Lom Ku god, you find yourself beset by
archeologists, graverobbers and other foes as you struggle to clean up the
temple grounds and appease the gods.  But watch out!  The gods are just
itching to kill those who fail them, or desecrate their temples!

This module is shareware at a cost of $2 and requires the Dungeon V2 archive
to work.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HouseOfFright"
@NEXT "Support"
@PREV "ChangKu"
@TOC "Main"

Five stories high, from basement to attic, the house of your ancestors will
be yours, if you can find the will.  As if that wasn't enough, the damned
place is haunted!  Ghosts, devils and demons hound you at every turn as you
scramble through the hallways, in search of the will.

This module is shareware at a cost of $2 and requires the Dungeon V2 archive
to work.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Support"
@NEXT "Progress"
@PREV "Reminder"
@TOC "Main"
At present, there are two locations from which you can get information and
copies of FBN programs.

@{"CyberSpace BBS" LINK "CyberSpace"} is the main distribution site for the FBN products.  Most
questions about FBN should be sent here because that's where I'll be most
of the time.

@{"The Sixth Dimension BBS" LINK "Sixth"} is the newest member of the FBN team.  You can find
all the FBN Amiga programs at this location as well.

@ENDNODE

